    "exhibits remarkable capabilities that are strikingly close to human-level performance, thereby showing early signs of general intelligence [3].",
    "They also warn us about the risks of this AI technology, stressing that 'great care would have to be taken on alignment and safety' [3 p.2].",
    "Third, there are AI experts worldwide who are monitoring the development of AI and expressing concern over the rapid pace of its innovation.",
    "Here the most prominent example, which we use in this paper to critically discuss the seemingly out-of-control nature of AI development, is the Future of Life Institute's (FLI) open letter published in March 2023.The letter in question was written and then endorsed by prominent AI scientists and public intellectuals such as Max Tegmark, Stuart Russell and Yuval Noah Harari, asking all AI companies to pause the development of AI systems with a computational power akin or superior to that of GPT-4 for six months [4].",
    "Moreover, the letter calls on governments from all around the world to impose a moratorium on AI development should AI companies like OpenAI and Google keep operating business as usual."
